React Native Custom Fonts

1st Step 
create folder name ==> fonts

2nd Step
Add some custom fonts in it.

3rd Step
cut fonts folder and past it in this directory:
../android/app/src/main/assets
OR
Project/assets

last step
create file name ==> react-native.config.js
and past some data in it.

module.exports = {
    project: {
      ios: {},
      android: {}, // grouped into "project"
    },
    assets: ["./assets/fonts/"], // stays the same
};

then just run in terminal ==> npx react-native-asset


